On chromatography paper, hydrophobic barriers are made using the polymer PDMS, which has a very flexible character. This approach involves moving substrates in different directions under the control of a printing table. The chromatography paper is covered with a nylon mesh screen stencil that has been designed according to specifications. After that, PDMS is applied to the surface and rubbed into the chromatography paper to create a pattern over the paper. The patterned paper is dried for 30 min at 120 ∘C\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
