				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$O_2$$\end{document}. Noh and Shim [188] reported another enzymatic fuel cell by immobilizing enzyme (glucose oxidases) molecules to the electrode surface in order to further lower the cost and extend the life of the fuel cell up to 16 days. The power density and open circuit voltage produced by the conversion of glucose into gluconic acid and hydrogen peroxide are 0.78 mW cm2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
