				\begin{document}$$cm^2$$\end{document} and 0.48 V, respectively. Using graphite electrodes attached to conductive wires through silver adhesive paste on a Y-shaped filter paper strip, Arun et al. [189] created a capillarity-mediated fuel cell. Inlet channels were soaked in a solution of sulfuric acid (oxidant) and formic acid (fuel). Formic acid produced 32 mW cm2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
